WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:01:56.990 --> 00:01:59.240
Easy. boy.

3
00:03:12.230 --> 00:03:14.270
What do you expect?
They're savages.

4
00:03:14.400 --> 00:03:16.770
One lot steals a goat from another lot.

5
00:03:16.900 --> 00:03:19.230
before you know it
they're ripping each other to pieces.

6
00:03:19.360 --> 00:03:21.820
l've never seen wildlings do a thing like this.

7
00:03:21.950 --> 00:03:24.110
l never seen a thing like this.
not ever in my life.

8
00:03:24.240 --> 00:03:26.410
How close did you get?

9
00:03:26.530 --> 00:03:29.950
- Close as any man would.
- We should head back to the Wall.

10
00:03:32.580 --> 00:03:34.040
Do the dead frighten you?

11
00:03:34.170 --> 00:03:36.290
Our orders were to track the wildlings.

12
00:03:36.420 --> 00:03:39.630
We tracked them.
They won't trouble us no more.

13
00:03:39.760 --> 00:03:42.170
You don't think he'll ask us how they died?

14
00:03:44.430 --> 00:03:46.220
Get back on your horse.

15
00:03:50.930 --> 00:03:53.440
Whatever did it to them
could do it to us.

16
00:03:53.560 --> 00:03:55.150
They even killed the children.

17
00:03:56.110 --> 00:03:58.110
lt's a good thing we're not children.

18
00:03:59.480 --> 00:04:02.280
You want to run away south.
run away.

19
00:04:02.400 --> 00:04:05.320
Of course.
they will behead you as a deserter.

20
00:04:05.450 --> 00:04:07.570
lf l don't catch you first.

21
00:04:09.950 --> 00:04:12.250
Get back on your horse.

22
00:04:12.370 --> 00:04:14.710
l won't say it again.

23
00:04:45.820 --> 00:04:48.320
Your dead men seem
to have moved camp.

24
00:04:49.030 --> 00:04:50.700
They were here.

25
00:04:54.080 --> 00:04:55.750
See where they went.

26
00:05:42.250 --> 00:05:44.130
What is it?

27
00:05:45.420 --> 00:05:46.550
lt's...

28
00:09:49.630 --> 00:09:52.090
Go on. Father's watching.

29
00:09:54.300 --> 00:09:56.010
And your mother.

30
00:10:02.180 --> 00:10:05.520
Fine work. as always.
Well done.

31
00:10:05.640 --> 00:10:07.310
Thank you.

32
00:10:07.440 --> 00:10:11.270
l love the detail that you've managed
to get in these corners.

33
00:10:11.400 --> 00:10:13.190
Quite beautiful.

34
00:10:13.320 --> 00:10:15.190
The stitching...

35
00:10:15.320 --> 00:10:17.530
Oh. no. no. no. This stitch is very...

36
00:10:19.240 --> 00:10:21.200
- lt's beautiful.
- Thank you.

37
00:10:36.380 --> 00:10:39.130
And which one of you
was a marksman at ten?

38
00:10:40.180 --> 00:10:41.680
Keep practicing. Bran.

39
00:10:43.850 --> 00:10:45.810
Go on.

40
00:10:45.930 --> 00:10:48.600
Don't think too much. Bran.

41
00:10:51.020 --> 00:10:52.190
Relax your bow arm.

42
00:11:05.330 --> 00:11:06.830
- Quick. Bran!
- Faster.

43
00:11:08.410 --> 00:11:10.410
Lord Stark!

44
00:11:12.460 --> 00:11:13.500
My lady.

45
00:11:14.540 --> 00:11:16.750
A guardsman just rode in from the hills.

46
00:11:16.880 --> 00:11:19.880
They've captured a deserter
from the Night's Watch.

47
00:11:23.180 --> 00:11:25.300
Get the lads to saddle their horses.

48
00:11:25.430 --> 00:11:27.390
Do you have to?

49
00:11:27.520 --> 00:11:29.600
He swore an oath. Cat.

50
00:11:29.730 --> 00:11:31.730
Law is law. my lady.

51
00:11:32.730 --> 00:11:34.810
Tell Bran he's coming too.

52
00:11:36.730 --> 00:11:38.320
Ned.

53
00:11:38.440 --> 00:11:40.740
Ten is too young
to see such things.

54
00:11:40.860 --> 00:11:42.400
He won't be a boy forever.

55
00:11:44.410 --> 00:11:46.070
And winter is coming.

56
00:12:05.220 --> 00:12:07.430
Good lad. go run back and get the rest.

57
00:12:13.560 --> 00:12:15.150
White walkers.

58
00:12:15.270 --> 00:12:17.980
l saw the white walkers.

59
00:12:18.110 --> 00:12:19.980
White walkers.

60
00:12:20.110 --> 00:12:23.150
The white walkers. l saw them.

61
00:12:31.950 --> 00:12:33.580
l know l broke my oath.

62
00:12:34.790 --> 00:12:36.290
And l know l'm a deserter.

63
00:12:37.170 --> 00:12:39.840
l should have gone back to the Wall
and warned them. but...

64
00:12:41.010 --> 00:12:43.010
l saw what l saw.

65
00:12:43.130 --> 00:12:44.670
l saw the white walkers.

66
00:12:46.640 --> 00:12:48.470
People need to know.

67
00:12:50.640 --> 00:12:52.470
lf you can get word to my family...

68
00:12:52.600 --> 00:12:54.890
tell them l'm no coward.

69
00:12:55.020 --> 00:12:56.980
Tell them l'm sorry.

70
00:13:14.000 --> 00:13:15.660
Forgive me. Lord.

71
00:13:20.040 --> 00:13:22.210
ln the name of Robert
of the House Baratheon.

72
00:13:22.340 --> 00:13:24.300
- the first of his name...
- Don't look away.

73
00:13:24.420 --> 00:13:27.260
- ..King of the Andals and the First Men...
- Father will know if you do.

74
00:13:27.380 --> 00:13:30.720
..Lord of the Seven Kingdoms
and protector of the realm.

75
00:13:30.850 --> 00:13:33.720
l. Eddard of the House Stark.

76
00:13:33.850 --> 00:13:36.390
Lord of Winterfell
and Warden of the North.

77
00:13:36.520 --> 00:13:38.980
sentence you to die.

78
00:13:53.790 --> 00:13:55.450
You did well.

79
00:14:23.650 --> 00:14:25.110
You understand why l did it?

80
00:14:25.230 --> 00:14:27.110
Jon said he was a deserter.

81
00:14:27.240 --> 00:14:29.780
But do you understand
why l had to kill him?

82
00:14:29.910 --> 00:14:31.530
"Our way is the old way"?

83
00:14:33.160 --> 00:14:36.830
The man who passes the sentence
should swing the sword.

84
00:14:37.870 --> 00:14:40.250
ls it true he saw the white walkers?

85
00:14:42.290 --> 00:14:45.250
The white walkers have been gone
for thousands of years.

86
00:14:46.420 --> 00:14:47.920
So he was lying?

87
00:14:52.430 --> 00:14:54.760
A madman sees what he sees.

88
00:15:20.710 --> 00:15:22.620
What is it?

89
00:15:25.000 --> 00:15:26.670
Mountain lion?

90
00:15:28.050 --> 00:15:30.380
There are no mountain lions
in these woods.

91
00:16:16.550 --> 00:16:18.350
lt's a freak.

92
00:16:19.720 --> 00:16:21.020
lt's a direwolf.

93
00:16:30.280 --> 00:16:32.530
Tough old beast.

94
00:16:34.820 --> 00:16:36.910
There are no direwolves
south of the Wall.

95
00:16:37.780 --> 00:16:39.080
Now there are five.

96
00:16:40.700 --> 00:16:42.370
You want to hold it?

97
00:16:46.920 --> 00:16:48.420
Where will they go?

98
00:16:48.540 --> 00:16:50.250
Their mother's dead.

99
00:16:50.380 --> 00:16:51.920
They don't belong down here.

100
00:16:52.050 --> 00:16:55.840
Better a quick death.
They won't last without their mother.

101
00:16:55.970 --> 00:16:57.970
- Right. Give it here.
- No!

102
00:16:58.100 --> 00:16:59.760
Put away your blade.

103
00:16:59.890 --> 00:17:02.810
- l take orders from your father. not you.
- Please. Father!

104
00:17:02.930 --> 00:17:04.730
l'm sorry. Bran.

105
00:17:04.850 --> 00:17:05.890
Lord Stark?

106
00:17:07.690 --> 00:17:09.190
There are five pups.

107
00:17:10.570 --> 00:17:12.650
One for each of the Stark children.

108
00:17:12.780 --> 00:17:15.280
The direwolf is the sigil of your house.

109
00:17:16.660 --> 00:17:18.870
They were meant to have them.

110
00:17:24.120 --> 00:17:26.290
You will train them yourselves.

111
00:17:26.420 --> 00:17:28.290
You will feed them yourselves.

112
00:17:28.420 --> 00:17:31.290
And if they die. you will bury them yourselves.

113
00:17:39.930 --> 00:17:41.640
What about you?

114
00:17:42.510 --> 00:17:44.180
l'm not a Stark.

115
00:17:44.310 --> 00:17:46.390
Get on.

116
00:17:56.450 --> 00:17:57.900
What is it?

117
00:18:02.120 --> 00:18:05.620
The runt of the litter.
That one's yours. Snow.

118
00:19:05.810 --> 00:19:08.980
As your brother.
l feel it's my duty to warn you...

119
00:19:10.230 --> 00:19:12.230
you worry too much.

120
00:19:12.350 --> 00:19:15.690
- lt's starting to show.
- And you never worry about anything.

121
00:19:16.980 --> 00:19:20.900
When we were seven and you jumped off
the cliffs at Casterly Rock.

122
00:19:21.030 --> 00:19:25.410
100-foot drop into the water...
you were never afraid.

123
00:19:25.530 --> 00:19:28.160
There was nothing to be afraid of
until you told Father.

124
00:19:28.290 --> 00:19:31.870
"We're Lannisters.
Lannisters don't act like fools."

125
00:19:34.290 --> 00:19:37.840
- What if Jon Arryn told someone?
- But who would he tell?

126
00:19:39.210 --> 00:19:40.340
My husband.

127
00:19:40.470 --> 00:19:44.220
lf he told the king. both our heads would be
skewered on the city gates by now.

128
00:19:45.760 --> 00:19:48.890
Whatever Jon Arryn knew or didn't know.
it died with him.

129
00:19:49.770 --> 00:19:51.600
And Robert will choose
a new Hand of the King.

130
00:19:51.730 --> 00:19:55.310
someone to do his job while he's off
fucking boars and hunting whores.

131
00:19:55.440 --> 00:19:57.110
Or is it the other way around?

132
00:19:58.650 --> 00:20:00.990
And life will go on.

133
00:20:01.110 --> 00:20:03.700
You should be the Hand of the King.

134
00:20:04.570 --> 00:20:06.410
That's an honor l can do without.

135
00:20:06.530 --> 00:20:08.160
Their days are too long.

136
00:20:08.290 --> 00:20:09.950
their lives are too short.

137
00:20:49.490 --> 00:20:50.700
All these years.

138
00:20:50.830 --> 00:20:53.960
and l still feel like an outsider
when l come here.

139
00:20:55.790 --> 00:20:57.460
You have five northern children.

140
00:20:58.710 --> 00:21:01.000
You're not an outsider.

141
00:21:01.130 --> 00:21:03.630
l wonder if the old gods agree.

142
00:21:04.880 --> 00:21:06.760
lt's your gods with all the rules.

143
00:21:13.520 --> 00:21:15.850
l am so sorry. my love.

144
00:21:16.980 --> 00:21:20.610
- Tell me.
- There was a raven from King's Landing.

145
00:21:22.730 --> 00:21:24.280
Jon Arryn is dead.

146
00:21:24.400 --> 00:21:26.900
A fever took him.

147
00:21:29.830 --> 00:21:31.950
l know he was like a father to you.

148
00:21:35.080 --> 00:21:38.120
- Your sister. the boy?
- They both have their health.

149
00:21:38.250 --> 00:21:40.250
gods be good.

150
00:21:50.510 --> 00:21:51.850
The raven brought more news.

151
00:21:53.970 --> 00:21:56.350
The king rides for Winterfell...

152
00:21:57.390 --> 00:22:00.190
with the queen and all the rest of them.

153
00:22:01.110 --> 00:22:03.440
lf he's coming this far north...

154
00:22:05.110 --> 00:22:07.030
there's only one thing he's after.

155
00:22:07.150 --> 00:22:10.530
You can always say no. Ned.

156
00:22:18.870 --> 00:22:22.590
We'll need plenty of candles
for Lord Tyrion's chamber.

157
00:22:22.710 --> 00:22:26.460
- l'm told he reads all night.
- l'm told he drinks all night.

158
00:22:26.590 --> 00:22:29.760
How much could he possibly drink?
A man of his...

159
00:22:29.890 --> 00:22:31.430
stature?

160
00:22:31.550 --> 00:22:34.430
We've brought up eight barrels of ale
from the cellar.

161
00:22:34.560 --> 00:22:35.770
Perhaps we'll find out.

162
00:22:35.890 --> 00:22:37.730
ln any case. candles.

163
00:22:43.860 --> 00:22:46.780
Why is your mother so dead set on us
getting pretty for the king?

164
00:22:46.900 --> 00:22:49.650
lt's for the queen. l bet.
l hear she's a sleek bit of mink.

165
00:22:49.780 --> 00:22:51.820
l hear the prince is a right royal prick.

166
00:22:51.950 --> 00:22:55.410
Think of all those southern girls he gets to stab
with his right royal prick.

167
00:22:57.330 --> 00:22:59.460
Go on. Tommy. shear him good.

168
00:22:59.580 --> 00:23:01.870
He's never met a girl he likes better
than his own hair.

169
00:23:38.870 --> 00:23:41.540
Gods. but they grow fast.

170
00:23:44.000 --> 00:23:45.500
Brandon!

171
00:23:45.630 --> 00:23:48.630
l saw the king.
He's got hundreds of people.

172
00:23:48.760 --> 00:23:51.840
How many times have l told you?
No climbing.

173
00:23:51.970 --> 00:23:54.930
But he's coming right now. down our road.

174
00:24:01.940 --> 00:24:04.350
l want you to promise me.

175
00:24:04.480 --> 00:24:06.150
no more climbing.

176
00:24:10.990 --> 00:24:12.150
l promise.

177
00:24:14.320 --> 00:24:17.370
- Do you know what?
- What?

178
00:24:17.490 --> 00:24:19.700
You always look at your feet
before you lie.

179
00:24:21.870 --> 00:24:23.620
Run and find your father.

180
00:24:23.750 --> 00:24:25.790
Tell him the king is close.

181
00:25:10.210 --> 00:25:13.590
Where's Arya?
Sansa. where's your sister?

182
00:25:23.890 --> 00:25:26.060
- Hey. hey. hey. hey.
- Oh.

183
00:25:26.190 --> 00:25:28.100
What are you doing with that on?

184
00:25:30.520 --> 00:25:32.610
Go on.

185
00:25:33.990 --> 00:25:35.650
Move!

186
00:26:57.820 --> 00:26:59.650
Your Grace.

187
00:27:04.160 --> 00:27:05.830
You've got fat.

188
00:27:17.920 --> 00:27:19.470
- Cat!
- Your Grace.

189
00:27:23.600 --> 00:27:27.060
Nine years... Why haven't l seen you?
Where the hell have you been?

190
00:27:27.180 --> 00:27:30.730
Guarding the North for you. Your Grace.
Winterfell is yours.

191
00:27:34.650 --> 00:27:37.190
- Where's the lmp?
- Will you shut up?

192
00:27:37.320 --> 00:27:38.820
Who have we here?

193
00:27:40.200 --> 00:27:41.530
You must be Robb.

194
00:27:44.490 --> 00:27:46.620
My. you're a pretty one.

195
00:27:48.040 --> 00:27:49.910
Your name is?

196
00:27:50.040 --> 00:27:51.410
Arya.

197
00:27:52.620 --> 00:27:55.210
Oh. show us your muscles.

198
00:27:56.540 --> 00:27:58.840
You'll be a soldier.

199
00:28:01.720 --> 00:28:04.130
That's Jaime Lannister.
the queen's twin brother.

200
00:28:04.260 --> 00:28:06.390
Would you please shut up?

201
00:28:15.940 --> 00:28:16.940
My queen.

202
00:28:18.230 --> 00:28:19.820
My queen.

203
00:28:19.940 --> 00:28:21.940
Take me to your crypt.
l want to pay my respects.

204
00:28:22.070 --> 00:28:23.900
We've been riding for a month. my love.

205
00:28:24.410 --> 00:28:26.030
Surely the dead can wait.

206
00:28:26.160 --> 00:28:28.030
Ned.

207
00:28:37.710 --> 00:28:38.920
Where's the lmp?

208
00:28:42.420 --> 00:28:44.430
Where is our brother?

209
00:28:44.550 --> 00:28:46.300
Go and find the little beast.

210
00:28:48.680 --> 00:28:50.350
Tell me about Jon Arryn.

211
00:28:51.600 --> 00:28:53.810
One minute he was fine and then...

212
00:28:55.020 --> 00:28:57.770
burned right through him.
whatever it was.

213
00:28:58.940 --> 00:29:00.940
l loved that man.

214
00:29:01.070 --> 00:29:02.400
We both did.

215
00:29:02.530 --> 00:29:06.860
He never had to teach you much.
but me? You remember me at 16?

216
00:29:06.990 --> 00:29:08.820
All l wanted to do

217
00:29:08.950 --> 00:29:11.580
was crack skulls and fuck girls.

218
00:29:11.700 --> 00:29:14.830
- He showed me what was what.
- Aye.

219
00:29:14.960 --> 00:29:17.580
Don't look at me like that.
lt's not his fault l didn't listen.

220
00:29:22.130 --> 00:29:24.170
l need you. Ned.

221
00:29:24.300 --> 00:29:27.970
down at King's Landing. not up here
where you're no damn use to anybody.

222
00:29:29.850 --> 00:29:31.640
Lord Eddard Stark...

223
00:29:32.600 --> 00:29:35.060
l would name you the Hand of the King.

224
00:29:39.520 --> 00:29:41.650
l'm not worthy of the honor.

225
00:29:41.780 --> 00:29:43.190
l'm not trying to honor you.

226
00:29:43.320 --> 00:29:45.030
l'm trying to get you to run my kingdom

227
00:29:45.150 --> 00:29:48.860
while l eat. drink and whore my way
to an early grave.

228
00:29:48.990 --> 00:29:50.820
Damn it. Ned. stand up.

229
00:29:52.370 --> 00:29:54.330
You helped me win the lron Throne.

230
00:29:54.450 --> 00:29:57.160
now help me keep the damn thing.

231
00:29:57.290 --> 00:29:59.670
We were meant to rule together.

232
00:29:59.790 --> 00:30:03.630
lf your sister had lived.
we'd have been bound by blood.

233
00:30:04.590 --> 00:30:06.170
Well. it's not too late.

234
00:30:07.840 --> 00:30:09.510
l have a son.
you have a daughter.

235
00:30:11.350 --> 00:30:13.010
We'll join our houses.

236
00:30:38.210 --> 00:30:41.170
lt is true what they say
about the northern girls.

237
00:30:49.380 --> 00:30:51.720
Did you hear the king's in Winterfell?

238
00:30:51.850 --> 00:30:53.470
l did hear something about that.

239
00:30:53.600 --> 00:30:55.760
And the queen and her twin brother.

240
00:30:55.890 --> 00:30:58.930
They say that he is the most handsome man
in the Seven Kingdoms.

241
00:30:59.060 --> 00:31:00.940
And the other brother?

242
00:31:01.060 --> 00:31:04.270
- The queen has two brothers?
- There's the pretty one...

243
00:31:05.480 --> 00:31:07.190
and there's the clever one.

244
00:31:08.490 --> 00:31:09.990
Mmm...

245
00:31:10.110 --> 00:31:12.360
l hear they call him the lmp.

246
00:31:12.490 --> 00:31:14.280
l hear he hates that nickname.

247
00:31:14.410 --> 00:31:17.790
Oh? l hear he's more than earned it.

248
00:31:17.910 --> 00:31:20.160
l hear he's a drunken little lecher.

249
00:31:20.290 --> 00:31:22.750
prone to all manner of perversions.

250
00:31:22.880 --> 00:31:24.670
Clever girl.

251
00:31:26.420 --> 00:31:28.260
We've been expecting you. Lord Tyrion.

252
00:31:29.590 --> 00:31:31.170
Have you?

253
00:31:31.300 --> 00:31:32.680
- Already?
- Oh!

254
00:31:35.600 --> 00:31:38.310
The gods gave me one blessing.

255
00:31:43.190 --> 00:31:45.690
- Don't get up.
- My lord.

256
00:31:45.820 --> 00:31:49.480
Should l explain to you the meaning of
a closed door in a whorehouse. brother?

257
00:31:49.610 --> 00:31:51.650
You have much to teach me. no doubt.

258
00:31:51.780 --> 00:31:54.950
but our sister craves your attention.

259
00:31:55.660 --> 00:31:57.660
She has odd cravings. our sister.

260
00:31:57.790 --> 00:31:59.830
A family trait.

261
00:31:59.950 --> 00:32:02.410
Now. the Starks are feasting us at sundown.

262
00:32:03.420 --> 00:32:07.380
- Don't leave me alone with these people.
- l'm sorry. l've begun the feast a bit early.

263
00:32:07.500 --> 00:32:10.840
And this is the first of many courses.

264
00:32:10.970 --> 00:32:13.180
l thought you might say that.

265
00:32:13.300 --> 00:32:15.930
But since we're short on time...

266
00:32:16.050 --> 00:32:17.350
Come on. girls.

267
00:32:23.310 --> 00:32:25.100
See you at sundown.

268
00:32:25.230 --> 00:32:27.310
Close the door!

